<h3><a name="OSG_iRODS_Program_of_Work_for_Sh"></a> OSG iRODS Program of Work for Shadow Storage Option </h3>
<p />
A plan sketch would be the following. The work starts with the Data Transfer function.
<p /> <ol>
<li> Install iRODS and add several distributed gridftp resources in a resource group.
</li> <li> Run various elementary rule files, with transfers only to local cache resource.
</li> <li> Create and run elementary rules using rulegen.
</li> <li> Run a rule with msiExecCmd invoking example hello script
</li> <li> Write an example script and run a rule with msiExecCmd invoking it.
</li> <li> Check the functionality of the Universal Mass Storage Driver with dummy scripts. 
</li> <li> Copy the Universal Mass Storage Driver as a new driver. <ol>
<li> Follow the documentation outlining the creation of a new driver.
</li></ol> 
</li> <li> Add a storage resource with the type of the new driver.
</li> <li> Before extending, recheck the functionality of the supported command subset.
</li> <li> Write a new univMSSFileWrite function. <ol>
<li> Include connection to client and protocol for return status
</li> <li> <strong>Study degree of difficulty before starting program of work.</strong>
</li></ol> 
</li> <li> Check the functionality with a file write and dummy driver script. <ol>
<li> Verify that pre and post-processing policy rules are invoked.
</li> <li> <strong>Study issues of why MSS is currently supported only as staging</strong> -asynchronicity?
</li></ol> 
</li> <li> Design actual univMSSFileWrite function. <ol>
<li> Do this design before starting the program of work.
</li></ol> 
</li> <li> Repeat the previous three steps for all other functions.
</li> <li> Devise and execute thorough transfer tests. <ol>
<li> In parallel -test each new function as it is written, continuous integration.
</li></ol> 
</li> <li> Propose modification of UMSD in iRODS code base to extended version.
</li> <li> Write and test rules using the msiExecCmd microservices for Discovery, Catalog, and Management functions.
</li></ol> 
<p />
